The '''Tanzanian masked weaver''' ('''''Ploceus reichardi'''''), or '''Tanganyika masked weaver''', is a species of [[bird]] in the [[Ploceidae|weaver]] family, Ploceidae. It is found in and around [[swamp]]s in south-western Tanzania and north-eastern Zambia. The [[Lufira masked weaver]] is sometimes treated as a [[subspecies]] of this bird.

